{
  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Sympy: Symbolic Computing {#sec-sympy}\n",
        "\n",
        "$~$\n",
        "\n",
        "[![](https://www.sympy.org/static/images/logo.png)](https://docs.sympy.org/latest/index.html)\n",
        "\n",
        "$~$\n",
        "\n",
        "## Importing sympy\n"
      ],
      "id": "86f8195e"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "import sympy\n",
        "from sympy import I, pi, oo\n",
        "sympy.init_printing()\n",
        "\n",
        "from IPython.display import display\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"sympy: \", sympy.__version__)"
      ],
      "id": "0ebc3cf7",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Symbols\n"
      ],
      "id": "edb19792"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "x = sympy.Symbol('x')\n",
        "print(x.is_real)"
      ],
      "id": "ffbf69a9",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "y = sympy.Symbol('y', real=True)\n",
        "y.is_real"
      ],
      "id": "b5c8d496",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "z = sympy.Symbol('z', complex=True)\n",
        "z.is_complex"
      ],
      "id": "7d2d8d3e",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "print(z.is_real)"
      ],
      "id": "b63f6af7",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n"
      ],
      "id": "507d6cad"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "x = sympy.Symbol('x')\n",
        "y = sympy.Symbol('y', positive=True)\n",
        "z = sympy.Symbol('z', negative=True)"
      ],
      "id": "27a8734e",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.sqrt(x**2)"
      ],
      "id": "0d10cf2d",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.sqrt(y**2)"
      ],
      "id": "0c02cd7c",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.sqrt(z**2)"
      ],
      "id": "558ab7d9",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n"
      ],
      "id": "3b5f5ac8"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "n1 = sympy.Symbol('n')\n",
        "n2 = sympy.Symbol('n', integer=True)\n",
        "n3 = sympy.Symbol('n', odd=True)\n",
        "n4 = sympy.Symbol('n', even=True)"
      ],
      "id": "fec4be72",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.cos(n1*pi)"
      ],
      "id": "ad40ce34",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.cos(n2*pi)"
      ],
      "id": "08a8c44e",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.cos(n3*pi)"
      ],
      "id": "5d57301b",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.cos(n4*pi)"
      ],
      "id": "640f0c91",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n"
      ],
      "id": "0176fc28"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "a, b, c = sympy.symbols('a, b, c', negative=True)"
      ],
      "id": "5c586d85",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "d, e, f = sympy.symbols('d, e, f', positive=True)"
      ],
      "id": "6a0aba97",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Numbers\n",
        "\n",
        "* We cannot directly use the built-in Python objects for integers, `int`, and floating-point numbers, `float`, and so on. Instead, `sympy` provides the classes `sympy.Integer` and `sympy.Float` for representing integers and floating-point numbers within the `sympy` framework\n",
        "\n",
        "* This distinction is important to be aware of when working with `sympy`, but fortunately we rarely\n",
        "need to concern ourselves with creating objects of type `sympy.Integer` and `sympy.Float` to representing\n",
        "specific numbers, $~$since `sympy` automatically promotes Python numbers to instances of these classes when they occur in `sympy` expressions\n"
      ],
      "id": "f4de6dd1"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "i = sympy.Integer(18)\n",
        "type(i)"
      ],
      "id": "36b89e0e",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "i.is_Integer, i.is_real, i.is_odd, i.is_even"
      ],
      "id": "b690f077",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "f = sympy.Float(2.3)\n",
        "type(f)"
      ],
      "id": "6d3d8ff7",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "f.is_Float, f.is_real, f.is_complex"
      ],
      "id": "2a7ebe21",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n"
      ],
      "id": "8f29e89d"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "i, f = sympy.sympify(19), sympy.sympify(2.3)\n",
        "type(i), type(f)"
      ],
      "id": "9d4ebc59",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Integer \n",
        "\n",
        "* While the `Symbol` with `integer=True` represents some integer, $\\,$the `Integer` instance represents a\n",
        "specific integer\n",
        "\n",
        "* For both cases, $\\,$the `is_integer` attribute is `True`, $\\,$but there is also an attribute `is_Integer`\n",
        "(note the capital `I`), $\\,$which is only `True` for `Integer` instances\n"
      ],
      "id": "d2f4e545"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "n = sympy.Symbol('n', integer=True)\n",
        "n.is_integer, n.is_Integer, n.is_positive, n.is_Symbol"
      ],
      "id": "95e94e56",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "i = sympy.Integer(19)\n",
        "i.is_integer, i.is_Integer, i.is_positive, i.is_Symbol"
      ],
      "id": "ec9ca416",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.Integer('19' *20)"
      ],
      "id": "fdc2994f",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.Integer('12_345_678'), sympy.Integer(12_345_678)"
      ],
      "id": "0f5a503a",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# great common division, leat common multiple\n",
        "sympy.igcd(36, 15), sympy.ilcm(7, 34)"
      ],
      "id": "7602ddab",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "* Integers in `sympy` are <font color='red'>**arbitrary precision**</font>, $\\,$meaning that they have <font color='blue'>no fixed lower and upper bounds</font>,\n",
        "$\\,$which is the case when representing integers with a specific bit-size, as, for example, in `numpy`\n"
      ],
      "id": "7b504285"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "i = sympy.Integer(19)\n",
        "i**100"
      ],
      "id": "87ebb7a5",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.factorial(100)"
      ],
      "id": "00f95fdb",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Float\n",
        "\n",
        "* Like `Integer`, $\\,$`Float` is <font color='red'>**arbitrary precision**</font>, $\\,$in contrast to Python’s built-in `float` type and the `float` types in `numpy`. $\\,$This means that any `Float` can represent a `float` with arbitrary number of decimals\n",
        "\n",
        "* When a `Float` instance is created using its constructor, $\\,$there are two arguments: the first argument is **a Python `float` or a string representing a floating-point number**, and the second (optional) argument is the **precision** (number of significant decimal digits) of the `Float` object\n"
      ],
      "id": "e03c9a1a"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# create a string representation with 25 decimals\n",
        "f'{0.3:.25f}'  "
      ],
      "id": "046c0a0c",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.Float(0.3, 25) "
      ],
      "id": "f0f94602",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.Float('0.3', 25)"
      ],
      "id": "b9c7447c",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.Float('123 456 789.123_456', '')"
      ],
      "id": "86260e51",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Rational\n"
      ],
      "id": "b64ad8d8"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "r0 = sympy.Rational(11, 13)\n",
        "r0"
      ],
      "id": "52066a2f",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "r0.p, r0.q"
      ],
      "id": "4067d90a",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "r1 = sympy.Rational(2, 3)\n",
        "r2 = sympy.Rational(4, 5)"
      ],
      "id": "9fc60314",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "r1 * r2"
      ],
      "id": "f5bad50b",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "r1 / r2"
      ],
      "id": "793c33eb",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.Rational(0.2), sympy.Rational('0.2')"
      ],
      "id": "6fb414ce",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Constants and special symbols\n",
        "\n",
        "$\\displaystyle \\gamma = \\lim_{n \\to \\infty} \\left( \\sum_{k=1}^n \\frac{1}{k} -\\ln n\\right)$\n"
      ],
      "id": "3d0c43e8"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.pi, sympy.E, sympy.EulerGamma, sympy.I, sympy.oo"
      ],
      "id": "bd2af501",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Functions\n"
      ],
      "id": "58b4954f"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "x, y, z = sympy.symbols('x, y, z')"
      ],
      "id": "eb629137",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "f = sympy.Function('f')\n",
        "type(f)"
      ],
      "id": "f263a889",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "f(x)"
      ],
      "id": "df2c497d",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "g = sympy.Function('g')(x, y, z)\n",
        "g"
      ],
      "id": "5393f274",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "g.free_symbols"
      ],
      "id": "61dfb72a",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n"
      ],
      "id": "d9e03245"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.sin"
      ],
      "id": "aebbac6a",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.sin(x)"
      ],
      "id": "c0474583",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sympy.sin(pi *1.5)"
      ],
      "id": "3d876270",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "n = sympy.Symbol('n', integer=True)\n",
        "sympy.sin(pi * n)"
      ],
      "id": "0ea3d02f",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "h = sympy.Lambda(x, x**2)\n",
        "h"
      ],
      "id": "d0648979",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "h(5)"
      ],
      "id": "4c0260c2",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "h(1 + x)"
      ],
      "id": "0d9969db",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Expressions\n"
      ],
      "id": "83003f68"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "x = sympy.Symbol('x')\n",
        "\n",
        "expr = 1 +2*x**2 +3*x**3\n",
        "expr"
      ],
      "id": "a2e10612",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "expr.args"
      ],
      "id": "66196d8c",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "expr.args[2]"
      ],
      "id": "1db65979",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "expr.args[2].args"
      ],
      "id": "aae54ba3",
      "execution_count": null,
